Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Information Technology Specialist Georgetown , ON Description Career Opportunity: Halton Hills Public LibraryInformation Technology SpecialistOne (1) Permanent Full-time positionJob Number: 202404The Town of Halton Hills is located on the Treaty Lands and Territory of the Mississauga of the Credit. Halton Hills, located 45 minutes from Toronto, is a unique and vibrant community with over 61,000 people and two well-established Library Branches. HHPL welcomes more than 250,000 visitors annually and more than 500,000 website visitors. We empower our patrons to learn, read, create, innovate, and experience at our Library. We strive to remove barriers and to foster an atmosphere of learning, support, understanding and inclusion. We employ over 35 professionally trained Library staff, who go above and beyond to provide stellar service to our patrons and deliver high-quality programs and relevant events. If this excites you, we’d love to continue the conversation.Position SummaryUnder the direction of the Manager of Content and Technologies, the Information Technology Specialist provides technical leadership for the implementation and maintenance of the library’s technical infrastructure, and effective utilization of technology within the organization. This position supports desktop applications, the integrated library system, the LAN/WAN network systems, cloud-based systems, servers, and online presence including website and digital library resources. This position provides project management for selected library technology and assists in the selection, management, deployment, and integration of new technology.Position ResponsibilitiesThese responsibilities indicate the general nature and level of work expected. It is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties or responsibilities required by the incumbent. The incumbent may be asked to perform other duties as required and as the nature of library services evolve.Systems and Application Management Install, setup and administer computer network servers and workstations Maintain and administer the library’s automated telephone contact solution Maintain and administer the library’s website in conjunction with other assigned staff Maintain and administer the integrated library system (ILS), including upgrades, updates, user accounts and integration of eResources, and peripheralsProject Management Provide technical leadership, implementation, and support for technology projects Liaise with staff, vendors and others to achieve effective implementation of projects Recommend research and plan the implementation of new technology In conjunction with Town, determine and plan for connectivity and infrastructure upgrades and changes Develop and implement communication plans to roll out new technology including training and support documentation, ongoing learning support, installation, and technical supportTechnical Support Provide timely and professional on-site and telephone support to resolve hardware, software, network, and operating system issues. Work with Town to assign support tickets Provide database support activities, such as implementation, backup and recovery, testing and upgrades. Support off-site technology through remote access and make service calls as required.Supervision Assess technical competencies of staff and assist with training Hire, train, supervise and evaluate I.T. co-op students.Administration Assist in developing and monitoring expenditures for operating and capital budgets for section Provide advice on modification or improvement of Library’s infrastructure Perform other job-related duties as assignedQualificationsEssential University degree in Information Technology or other related discipline Five (5) years’ experience in a technology related environmentTechnical Competencies Proven technical skills in desktop software knowledge and a superior understanding of Microsoft operating systems and office automation software Knowledge of programming languages (python, RUBY, PHP, JavaScript), cloud technologies, Azure, and AI Proven understanding of LAN/WAN network systems Experience with Microsoft Server administration and active directory Experience with firewall, VPN technologies, anti-virus/malware applications Familiarity with wide range of technology including: tablets, smartphones, 3D printers and scanners Knowledge of the management and maintenance of integrated library systems Knowledge of application data privacy practices and laws Familiarity with cybersecurity principles, best practices and tools A valid driver’s license and own transportationDesirable PMP designation CompTIA, ITIL Foundation certificationHours: 35 hours per week. May include evenings and weekends in both Acton and Georgetown Branches.Salary: $84,360 - $100,428 + competitive benefits and pension Application Deadline: Sunday, April 14, 2024, at 5pmStart Date: May 2024To Apply:Qualified candidates may submit a detailed cover letter and resume in confidence to the Library by 5:00 p.m. on Sunday, April 14, 2024. Those candidates offered an interview will be required to provide the names and contact information of three references at that time.Please identify the title of the position and the job number that you are applying for in your cover letter and on the Resume Submission Portal where indicated. Please apply using only one method of application below. Online: Resumé Submission Portal: www.hhpl.ca/ResumePortal (preferred) Mail:Lori Mazza Brenton, Executive Assistant Halton Hills Public Library 9 Church Street Georgetown, Ontario L7G 2A3RE: Information Technology Specialist – Content and TechnologiesWe thank all those who apply but advise that only those applicants selected for an interview will be contacted. The Halton Hills Public Library is an equal opportunity employer. Accommodations are available for all parts of the recruitment process. If contacted for an interview, please advise the Library’s Executive Assistant at 905-873-2681 Ext. 2523 of any measures you feel you need to enable you to be assessed in a fair and equitable manner. Information received relating to accommodation measures will be addressed confidentially. Compensation $84,360 - $100,428 + competitive benefits and pension Closes: 14 April, 2024 Halton Hills Public Library Georgetown , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
