opment including policies, selection and on-going maintenance as required. Acts as a liaison to local library boards.Qualifications, knowledge, and skills: Post graduate university degree in library or information science from an accredited program. Previous library management experience of a progressively more responsible nature. Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to lead a diverse group of people. Experience leading and coaching staff in a unionized workplace. Strong project management and strategic thinking abilities. Ability to demonstrate creativity, innovation, and research skills. Demonstrate experience delivering goals that support the strategic priorities of an organization. Previous experience with collection management. Excellent oral and written communication skills, including tact and diplomacy. Ability to sustain cooperative, productive relationships with staff and patrons. Experience working with a Board of Directors is an asset. A valid driver’s license and the ability to drive throughout the region as required. Criminal Record Check satisfactory to the employer will be required.Remuneration:Salary: $80,542-$90,550Includes a comprehensive benefit package, including health, dental and vison, life insurance, long term disability, defined pension plan (MEPP) and professional development opportunities.Interested applicants are requested to submit a current resume and cover letter to the Library Director (khebig@wheatland.sk.ca) by March 31st, 2024.Only applicants who are selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $80,542-$90550 Closes: 31 March, 2024 Wheatland Regional Library Saskatoon , SK Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
