lan and recommend changes to the Federation Board and the Library Directors’ Advisory Group (LDAG) to act as liaison to all member libraries and committees of the Federation Board to communicate with and regularly report to the Chairperson and LDAG to work with the Public Libraries Branch, other federations and other organizations locally, regionally and provincially to achieve common goals to act as secretary to the Federation Board and in cooperation with the Chairperson, prepare agendas for meetings to prepare reports for the Federation, including the annual Provincial Grant Report to make necessary arrangements for meetings of the Federation Board, the LDAG and other committees/teams to draft policy and procedures for the Federation and present same to the Federation Board and LDAG for approval to plan workshops, programs, author tours, and speakers as requested by the member libraries and/or Federation Board to oversee and monitor the development of the Federation’s Web site ensuring accuracy and currency of information to maintain the Federation files and passwords to negotiate with vendors and seek new services / product suppliers as required to perform additional services as directed by the Federation Board Financial Management to assist in the preparation of the annual budget and administer same to seek additional funding as required to perform or oversee book-keeping functions including: receipt and verification of invoices management of accounts receivable and payable issuing cheques payroll monthly banking reconciliation financial reporting to the Federation Board Reporting Relationship: The Director reports to the Chairperson of the IslandLink Library Federation Board. Salary and benefits: $35.00 - $37.00 per hour, (approx. 17.5 hours a week) plus a percentage in lieu of benefits. Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Application: Please submit your letter of application and resume, by email to: Ms. Selina Smith, Chair; IslandLink Library Federation Board office@islandlink.ca Applications close on March 31, 2024.We thank all applicants but can only contact those who are selected for an interview. For more information about the IslandLink Library Federation please access our website: .https://islandlink.bc.libraries.coop/ Compensation $35.00-$37.00 per hour Closes: 31 March, 2024 IslandLink Library Federation Nanaimo , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
